{
  "texts": [
    "As quality of convolutional network predictions tends to deteriorate near image boundaries, corgie allows the input chunks to overlap, combining their results either through cropping or soft blending.",
    "Processing of an individual chunk constitutes an atomic task, which will be assigned to one of the distributed workers.",
    "Instead of creating a static computation graph which encodes all of the dependencies between tasks, which may introduce overhead when the number of tasks is large, corgie uses dynamic task dispatch.",
    "More specifically, each processing step is defined as a Job.",
    "Upon being called, a job will yield either a set of tasks or a Barrier dependency, indicating that all of the tasks previously yielded by this job must be completed before the job can proceed."
  ]
}